article.headline: UTEP 95, UC Riverside 55
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Dale Vanwright and Stefon Jackson scored 18 points apiece to help lead Texas-El Paso in a 95-55 rout of UC Riverside on Tuesday night. Texas-El Paso (8-6) scored first and led throughout the game, taking a 46-28 lead into halftime. The Miners took their biggest lead, a 46-point margin, at 9:31 in the second half. Vanwright was 7-for-9 from the field, including 3-for-3 from behind the arc. Jackson was 5-for-11 from the field and 6-for-7 on free throws. Maurice Thomas added 12 points for the Miners and led the team with nine rebounds. Chris Johnson led UC Riverside (3-11) with a game-high 28 points, including 6-for-9 3-point shooting. Henrik Thomsen added 11. Dedrick Bates came off the bench to score 11 points and lead the team with seven rebounds. Texas El-Paso shot 50 percent from the field to 39 percent for UC Riverside. Texas-El Paso won the rebounding contest 42-24.
